  "text": "If you’re a Mac gamer and you love free games, you won’t want to miss out on this deal; Borderlands 2, the classic popular first-person action RPG shooter, is free to download this weekend on Steam (until the morning of June 8 at 10am PDT). And because it’s on Steam, you’ll be able to play Borderlands 2 on a Mac, Windows PC, or Linux machine. Borderlands 2 is a quirky space western dystopian science fiction themed action RPG shooter that has some neat cell-shaded graphics, a compelling story, and some odd humor and characters too. The game is set in a fictional world and is story driven action roleplaying, so don’t be expecting a quick game of Minesweeper. So, why not grab Borderlands 2 for free while it’s available this weekend? How to Download Borderlands 2 for Free on Steam You will need to have Steam and a Steam account to be able to download and play Borderlands 2 for free. If you don’t have Steam and a Steam account, you can create one at https://store.steampowered.com/. We’re assuming you have already completed this task and have a Steam account: Launch Steam and login to your Steam account (free) Either click here to go to the Borderlands 2 page on Steam or search for “Borderlands 2” within Steam and go to the Borderlands 2 page Look for where it says “Get Borderlands 2” and choose “Add to Account” (free until June 8) Choose to download and install Borderlands 2, when the game is finished downloading click on “Play” to launch Borderlands 2 Enjoy the game! You can play through the single player campaign, or play in multiplayer mode. Since BorderLands 2 was first released in 2012, the system requirements are quite generous. I was able to turn up every graphics setting on my Apple Silicon MacBook Air to the highest setting, and the game ran flawlessy. Have you played Borderlands 2 before? Are you going to download the game while it’s free? Share your thoughts in the comments.",
